<subSubSection box="[199,1251,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,392]" box="[199,1251,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,151,176]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Etymology.</emphasis>
The epithet references the ethnic group Tzotzil from the Altos de 
<collectingRegion box="[1075,1165,151,176]" country="Mexico" name="Chiapas" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Chiapas</collectingRegion>
region.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="405" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,151,392]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,188,213]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Distribution.</emphasis>
Pine-oak and tropical montane rain forests of 
<collectingRegion box="[888,981,188,213]" country="Mexico" name="Chiapas" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Chiapas</collectingRegion>
, suggesting its distribution may include mountains of 
<collectingRegion box="[305,389,224,248]" country="Mexico" name="Oaxaca" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Oaxaca</collectingRegion>
in the Chimalapas region and 
<collectingRegion box="[731,821,223,248]" country="Mexico" name="Chiapas" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Chiapas</collectingRegion>
province (
<emphasis box="[942,953,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">s</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Morrone" box="[967,1130,223,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405" refString="Morrone, J. (2005) Hacia una sintesis biogeografica de Mexico. Revista Mexicana de Biodiversidad, 76 (2), 207 - 252." type="journal article" year="2005">Morrone 2005</bibRefCitation>
) to 
<collectingRegion box="[1173,1294,223,248]" country="Guatemala" name="Guatemala" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">
<collectingCountry box="[1173,1294,223,248]" name="Guatemala" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Guatemala</collectingCountry>
</collectingRegion>
(
<figureCitation box="[1310,1393,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 57 – 58. 57" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1876,1899]" captionTargetBox="[514,1092,1007,1817]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[470,1116,949,1856]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 57 – 58. 57 — Map of collecting localities for Colletes jobeli, C. isabelae, C. jaliscoensis and C. nigerrima. 58 — Map of collecting localities for C. solari, C. tzotzilis, C. chiaPensis, and C. guatemalensis." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1051949/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,260,285]" pageId="4" pageNumber="405">Remarks.</emphasis>
Some females have a small notch on the anterior margin of clypeus and punctures on scape. Basal area of propodeum with longitudinal striae, which form pits with horizontal striae. Males may present scutum with shallower and sparse punctures on the anterior margin, mesosoma with shallower punctures on the lateral region, and metasomal terga with duller iridescence.
</paragraph>
